cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) because it focuses on evaluating word vector representations using linguistic resources. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) because it proposes a new evaluation metric for word vectors. Additionally, it could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) because it involves training neural networks to learn word vectors, and cs.CV (Computer Vision) because word vectors are often used in natural language processing tasks related to image and video analysis.
